    <h1>Value at Risk</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">MIT OCW 18.S096 + 15.450 (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Value at Risk (VaR)</strong> answers one question: what is the worst loss you can expect over a given horizon at a given confidence level? Expected Shortfall (CVaR) asks the harder follow-up: given that you exceed VaR, how bad is it on average?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: VaR / CVaR on a loss distribution -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
